FuncDef: The display nat64 vsuf status command displays information about the NAT64 license status.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the slot ID of a service board.
The value is a string of 1 to 15 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To view information about the NAT64 license status, run the display nat64 vsuf status command. The command output contains the activation status, allocation information, and whether a service board can be detected.
Prerequisites
The NAT64 function has been enabled using the active nat64 vsuf command.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
